Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.52,0:46:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,go from perfect to more perfect\Nbecause it is the downside and the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.35,0:47:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,tragedies of the world that tend to\Nenergize uh the ambition to transcend
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.59,0:47:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it. To transcend it. Yeah.\NUh fear, of course, everybody knows this
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.96,0:47:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,one. the excitement of the danger, uh,\Ndramatizing it, um, the emotionalism,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.28,0:47:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course, fear has to do with, uh,\Nbeing on the front of the crest of the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.04,0:47:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,wave. And, um, just like grief is\Nclinging to the past, fear is
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.40,0:47:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,anticipating,\Nequinimity. And peace is to be right on
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.59,0:47:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the the peak of the the wave without\Nresisting this or without clinging to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.64,0:47:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that with neither clinging nor\Nresisting. Neither attraction nor
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.44,0:47:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,aversion.\NUh people have a an aversion unless
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.48,0:47:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,they're trained to stay cool. Uh\Nmen learn that in the military. You stay
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.96,0:47:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,cool. The bigger the danger, the more\Nthe more you stay cool. Nobody wants you
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.11,0:48:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to emotionalize. He's\Nkamicazi pilots's overhead and this
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.83,0:48:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,guy's blubbering over here isn't going\Nto be too much of a help when he's in a
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.68,0:48:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,20 mm anti-aircraft gun. Uh, he better\Nstay cool. So, there's no room for So,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.07,0:48:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,this allows you to see that when things\Nare really serious, emotionalizing
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.83,0:48:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,stops. Nobody's got time for\Nemotionalizing. Nobody's got time for
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.07,0:48:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,blubbering because everybody everybody's\Nlife is on the spot. So all
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.64,0:48:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,emotionalization is really a\Nself-indulgence.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.88,0:48:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Npeople have an aversion to staying calm
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.80,0:48:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of disaster. You hear\Npeople screaming all over. Why you'd
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.64,0:48:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,want to scream when your house is being\Ncarried away by a tornado is beyond me.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.40,0:48:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's the last time moment I\Nwould think about screaming. You know
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.04,0:48:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what I mean? I'm trying to hang on to\Nthe dog and hang on to the cat and
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.96,0:48:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going up through the air.\NWe'll leave the screaming till later,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.24,0:48:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.\NThe other thing interesting about the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.88,0:49:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Weather Channel, you know, they've got\Nquite a few uh hurricanes and tornadoes
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.44,0:49:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and things on there. Uh the number of\Npeople, the survivors of all these
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.07,0:49:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,disasters. We were watching it last\Nnight, the night before. Every one of
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.68,0:49:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,them mentioned how they prayed. Of\Ncourse, these are all survivors.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.83,0:49:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, "I prayed to God to help me."\NAnd she was an oriental lady. I was
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.92,0:49:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,pinned down hopelessly for 48 hours. No\Nwater, no food, nobody could get to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.72,0:49:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just prayed. I prayed. Almost\Nevery one of them survived the disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.28,0:49:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Mentioned how they prayed.\NThat was interesting. The other thing
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.59,0:49:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that was interesting is an occasional\None will tell you uh maybe about once a
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.11,0:49:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,year a survivor of a\Ntornado will tell you how they were
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.48,0:49:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,lifted up 50und feet in the air and they\Nwent into a state of sublime peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.59,0:50:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,A number of them did that. I was swirled\Nup into the air 100t over and then
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.11,0:50:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly a a great profound sense of\Npeace came upon me. If all those fields
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.44,0:50:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,get sucked up in a tornado,\Nit's a poor time to emotionalize, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.96,0:50:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You're 100 ft quiring in the air.\NNo time. You can blubber later, but
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.64,0:50:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,right now. All right. So, we'll let go\Nof fear. So we'll let go of fear then
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.64,0:50:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and perhaps see it as um uh the indul\Nindulgence of the child within us
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.35,0:50:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because when is fear appropriate?\NI don't know when is fear. Caution is a
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.96,0:50:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,different thing. Caution is not the same\Nthing. Caution is thinking, anticipating
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.16,0:50:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and u but it's not emotionalizing.\NUh fear is going into hysteria and
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.35,0:51:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,coming apart. You see, and you can't\Ncome apart if the situation is one of
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.16,0:51:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,real uh danger where you need to stay\Ncool. You have to learn to handle it
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.20,0:51:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,calmly.\NAll right? In the end, you can surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.11,0:51:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly and trust God. And you think\Nif we die, uh we die, you know, and I
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.31,0:51:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,related how\Nin World War II, this mine is right next
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.96,0:51:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to the mind sweeper and two of us\Nlooking over a gunnel here. And here
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.88,0:51:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,here's the horn sticking out about an\Ninch or two from the the ship. Another
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.11,0:51:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,another inch or two and boom. So uh you\Nknow he looked at me I said well worst
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.72,0:51:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,can happen is we blow up. So he said\Nyeah. So
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.68,0:51:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,worst thing happen so you blow up. So\Nbig deal you know what I mean? So even
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.07,0:51:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,facing death you see fearful\Nemotionalization
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.92,0:51:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is not even necessary because with\Nacceptance you transcend into serenity.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.07,0:51:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and he got it from me and I got it from\Nhim. I guess I got it from the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.11,0:52:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,near-death experience where I realized\Nthat fear was not it wasn't really a
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.28,0:52:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,near-death experience but what the\Npeople think is
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.80,0:52:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that um death is not a possibility.\NNow at a certain level everybody sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.16,0:52:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,knows that because when we calibrated a\Nnear-death experience shows a major jump
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.55,0:52:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in consciousness before and after the\Nexperience. Whereas out of body
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.88,0:52:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,experience you don't see any change at\Nall. Person who calibrates at 340 goes
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.92,0:52:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,out of body for the first time and comes\Nback in body later they still calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.80,0:52:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,at 340.\Nperson near death calibrates at 340.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.04,0:52:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They come back, they can maybe\Ncalibrate, you know, 560 or 570 or
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.55,0:52:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,something. And we asked why is that? And\Nwe got because out of body is merely
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.28,0:52:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencing that you're a spirit and\Nnot a body. And you know that already.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.80,0:52:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You've already spent eons as a spirit.\NAnd therefore, it's not a you haven't
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.35,0:52:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,learned anything. You knew that all\Nalong. So when you get out of the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.44,0:53:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you're you're back where it's more\Nfamiliar than being in a body. Being in
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.55,0:53:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a body is really actually strange. Being\Nout of a body is more familiar. So it's
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.44,0:53:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,not surprised you didn't learn anything\Nnew when you went out of body because
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.76,0:53:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you knew you that's who you were all\Nalong. You know that you you you are in
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.16,0:53:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,space wherever you think you are in\Nspace. Wherever you think you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.72,0:53:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you're there. So uh that's interesting.\NSo we let go of fear then of death by
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.80,0:53:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,total acceptance that death is not a\Npossibility and we surrender our life to
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.52,0:53:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,God. Trust trust God and if it's time to\Nblow up so you blow up.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.40,0:53:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay next\Nmore fear. Oh dear. Uh well the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.44,0:53:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,attraction is fears tend to proliferate.\NAnd of course you like to harbor our
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.24,0:53:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,fears and justify them. We like to\Nproject the cause as being out there out
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.28,0:53:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,there. The cause of the fear is out\Nthere. The cause of the fear is the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.35,0:54:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Komodo dragon. It's the commandment.\NHe's the one that's causing my fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.44,0:54:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, projecting\Nthe source as external.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.48,0:54:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, fear sees life as\Nstrictly physical, focuses on the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.07,0:54:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and the bottom fear of the ego is really\Ndeath. Uhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.64,0:54:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,\Nin surrendering a stack of fears, if you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.28,0:54:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,use the technique of then what? So the\Nyou take a fear. I'm going to lose my
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.96,0:54:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,car. Well, then what? Well, then I won't\Nhave transportation. Then what? Then
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.83,0:54:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll lose my job. Then what? Then you'll\Nhave to walk to work. Yeah, but there
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.92,0:54:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,aren't any jobs like that. Well, then\Nyou won't have any money. Yeah. Then
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.20,0:54:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,what? Then I'll be poor. Okay, so you're\Npoor. Then what? Then I'll starve to
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.83,0:54:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,death. Okay. So at the bottom of every\Nstack of fears is death. Physical death.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.68,0:54:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you say so what to physical\Ndeath, nothing scares you anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.68,0:54:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing really frightens you because the\Nbasic fear once you've surrendered
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.07,0:55:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,completely to to the physical death the\Nwhole stack is brought down. Remember
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.28,0:55:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,instar\Nis a big stack and at the bottom of that
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.80,0:55:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,stack is the fear of physical death. So\Nonce you've accepted physical death then
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.20,0:55:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,most of the fears that we have which are\Nfocused on the body and and loss of
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.40,0:55:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,possessions and things uh disappear. So\Nwe'll move on. You do that by
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.20,0:55:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,acceptance.\NThis is the one that really bothers most
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.20,0:55:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,people most of the time. You know fears\Ncome along and grief comes along etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.04,0:55:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,People are apathetic about certain\Nthings in their life. But the desire and
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.83,0:55:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,wantingness is the one that really\Nbothers the most people most of the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.92,0:55:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,time. Uh because of the attraction of\Nwinning, money, gain, control, getting
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.96,0:55:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,winning the election, approval, success,\Nfame,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.52,0:55:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,um acquisitions, conquest,\Nof course, being right.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.35,0:56:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Being right. People are willing to die\Nright and left for being right. They
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.83,0:56:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,would rather die and be right than not\Nbe right. The ego doesn't mind dumping
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.07,0:56:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,your body at all.\NRather than admit defeat, the ego will
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.11,0:56:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,walk you over the cliff.\NPeople die for illusions all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.31,0:56:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In my lifetime, a 100 million people,\Nprobably twice that, have died chasing
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.76,0:56:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,some illusion rather than admit that. I\Nmean, Chairman Mayo's economic uh
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.07,0:56:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,agricultural plan resulted in the\Nstarvation of three 30 million people.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.07,0:56:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Mayo's little red book. The faith in\NChairman Mayo, God bless him, resulted
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.16,0:56:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in the death of 30 million people by\Nstarvation. The greatest famine in all
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.28,0:56:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of history.\NAfter that, would you think Marxism
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.76,0:57:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe is wrong? No. we will spread it\Nfurther into the world. Okay. The
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.48,0:57:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,inability to learn to the pride pr pride\Nof the ego then uh
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.48,0:57:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,so the desire to be right to control\Nuh approval all these things we are very
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.20,0:57:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,familiar with because it's part of\Neveryday life. We all fear appearing
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.88,0:57:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,passive uh weak uh of failure uh poverty\Nuh losing and many people um
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.52,0:57:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,want to be noticed at all times. You see\Nthe extremes to which people go uh to be
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.72,0:57:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,noticed say anything no matter how\Noutrageous as long as you're on camera
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.07,0:57:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,or get on the camera. So we'll go next.\NThe dualities of anger
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.16,0:57:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is closer a little bit to the animal\Nworld because you feel expanded and
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.04,0:58:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,stirred up bigger than life with anger.\NGives you a feeling to dramatize and
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.16,0:58:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,emotionalize\Nand to be right and growl you. So the
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.72,0:58:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,animal in you growls and shows his teeth\Nand tries to win by intimidation. Uhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.55,0:58:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Last thing it wants is to be calm, be at\Npeace, afraid it'll appear weak, doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.64,0:58:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,want to give in, you know, and of\Ncourse, not wanting to see a bad guy go
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.48,0:58:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,free.\NUh, let go. The Buddhist said, you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.11,0:58:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,have to worry about getting even with\Nyour enemies because they will bring
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.83,0:58:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves down by their own hand. They\Nwill bring themselves down by their own
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.92,0:58:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,hand. And with consciousness\Ncalibration, of course, we affirm the
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.11,0:58:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,truth of that over and over. So, let's\Nmove to the next one. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.31,0:58:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Is this the next one?\N>> Oh, it is the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.55,0:59:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder I can't find the next one.\NOkay. Pride. We're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.28,0:59:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual pride. We're not talking about\Nself-esteem. Self-esteem is earned.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.35,0:59:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it's not ego inflating. Uh\Npride is something a projection that we
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.52,0:59:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,impose and it gives you status and it\Ngets you noticed and you get to be
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.28,0:59:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,superior. You get to be an insider.\NUh you get to be elite. Uh what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.11,0:59:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Politically elite politically correct.\NUh you get to be uh above the common
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.79,0:59:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,people.\Nwhich is of course the paradox of
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.83,0:59:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,egalitarianism\Nwhich is that all people are equal
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.88,0:59:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,value but some people are more valuable\Nthan others
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.83,0:59:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning us mainly.\NThe reason is because we're more
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.76,1:00:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,egalitarian than anybody else and that\Nmakes us superior to the rest of people.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.11,1:00:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So the downside which they is humility.\NUh the fear you may look down on, you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.96,1:00:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,may just be ignored because you're\Ncommon and ordinary. Um the worst of all
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.00,1:00:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,things of course is to be wrong. Uh and\Npeople would rather die than be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.96,1:00:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They do it all the time.\NWe'll see a whole another generation of
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.83,1:00:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,people uh dying rather than admitting\Nthat they were following a false
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.83,1:00:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,teacher, an error. Yeah. Move on next.\NUhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.11,1:00:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If what we're witnessing is creation\Nunfolding,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.24,1:00:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, evolution is creation\Nunfolding, then what we view as mistakes
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.68,1:01:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,really represent a success because they\Nthey
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.55,1:01:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstrate the outcome of a fallacy.\NIf 30 million people starve to death
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.83,1:01:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,according to a certain belief system,\Nthis is the automatic demonstration of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.40,1:01:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,falsity. So we see that falsity then\Ninstead of trying to prevent its
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.04,1:01:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,occurrence in the world, we try to\Ncounter it, but it serves its own
